Requirement Description: Peer Review For Deepwater Safety Report

Contracting Agency: Office Of Policy, Budget And Administration
Requirement Description:
Utilizing His Knowledge, Expertise, Training, And Experience, The Contractor Will Read, Analyze, And Provide Independent Peer Review Of The Draft Report Which Will Contain Analyses And Recommendations Developed By The Teams.  As A Result Of That Review, The Contractor Will Provide Comments, Suggestions, Advice, And Recommendations For Improving The Report And Achieving The Objectives In The Secretarial Order As Quoted Above.  

An Introductory Meeting With The Safety Oversight Board Is Scheduled To Take Place On Friday, August 6th  In Room 6616 At The Department Of The Interior.  The Contractor Is Requested To Be Present At And Participate In This Meeting.  During That Meeting The Board And The Contractor Will Share Initial Impressions Of The Draft Report And The Board Will Solicit The Initial Views Of The Contractor Regarding Areas In Need Of Additional Analysis, Refinement And Improvement As Well As Views About The Viability, Responsiveness, And Effectiveness Of The Recommendations.  The Board And The Contractor Will Also Discuss Scheduling And Logistics For The Week Ahead.  During The Weekend Of Saturday And Sunday, August 7th 驴 8th, The Board And The Contractor Will Meet At The Main Interior Building (room 6616) For The Purpose Of Further Reviewing The Draft Report.  
   
During The Week Of August 9th, The Board Will Meet At The Atrium Building, U.S. Department Of The Interior, 381 Elden Street, 2nd Floor Conference Room, Herndon, Virginia 20170 To Continue Its Discussions And Review And To Begin Editing Of The Draft Report.  Currently, The Board Anticipates Being Able To Circulate The Draft Report To Other Members Of The Secretary驴s Senior Leadership Time On Thursday, August 12th In Order To Solicit Their Views And Comments.  As A Result Of That Review, Subsequent Discussions With The Board And The Contractor Will Result In Further Editing And Refinement As The Week Continues.  While The Contractor Will Not Be Required To Be Physically Present As The Final Work Of The Board Continues During The Weekend Of August 14th-15th, The Board Requests That The Contractor Be Available By Telephone To Respond To Requests For Information And Input As Necessary.

Dates: 
1.	The Introductory Meeting Will Be Held On August 6, 2010 @1:00 P.M.
2.	Board Meetings At Which The Contractor Will Be Present Will Occur On August 6th - 8th, At The Department Of The Interior, 1849 C Street, N.W., Room 6616, Washington, D.C. 20240, And From August 9th -  August 13th, U.S. Department Of The Interior, 381 Elden Street, 2nd Floor Conference Room, Herndon, Virginia 20170.  Telephonic Availability Of The Contractor Is Requested On August 14th 驴 15th. 
2. Travel: Is Required For August 6th 驴 13th.
3. The Government Will Provide The Draft Safety Report Material To The Reviewer As Soon As It Is Available.

Contracting Agency: Office Of Policy, Budget And Administration
Requirement Description:
Utilizing His Knowledge, Expertise, Training, And Experience, The Contractor Will Read, Analyze, And Provide Independent Peer Review Of The Draft Report Which Will Contain Analyses And Recommendations Developed By The Teams.  As A Result Of That Review, The Contractor Will Provide Comments, Suggestions, Advice, And Recommendations For Improving The Report And Achieving The Objectives In The Secretarial Order As Quoted Above.  

An Introductory Meeting With The Safety Oversight Board Is Scheduled To Take Place On Friday, August 6th  In Room 6616 At The Department Of The Interior.  The Contractor Is Requested To Be Present At And Participate In This Meeting.  During That Meeting The Board And The Contractor Will Share Initial Impressions Of The Draft Report And The Board Will Solicit The Initial Views Of The Contractor Regarding Areas In Need Of Additional Analysis, Refinement And Improvement As Well As Views About The Viability, Responsiveness, And Effectiveness Of The Recommendations.  The Board And The Contractor Will Also Discuss Scheduling And Logistics For The Week Ahead.  During The Weekend Of Saturday And Sunday, August 7th 驴 8th, The Board And The Contractor Will Meet At The Main Interior Building (room 6616) For The Purpose Of Further Reviewing The Draft Report.  
   
During The Week Of August 9th, The Board Will Meet At The Atrium Building, U.S. Department Of The Interior, 381 Elden Street, 2nd Floor Conference Room, Herndon, Virginia 20170 To Continue Its Discussions And Review And To Begin Editing Of The Draft Report.  Currently, The Board Anticipates Being Able To Circulate The Draft Report To Other Members Of The Secretary驴s Senior Leadership Time On Thursday, August 12th In Order To Solicit Their Views And Comments.  As A Result Of That Review, Subsequent Discussions With The Board And The Contractor Will Result In Further Editing And Refinement As The Week Continues.  While The Contractor Will Not Be Required To Be Physically Present As The Final Work Of The Board Continues During The Weekend Of August 14th-15th, The Board Requests That The Contractor Be Available By Telephone To Respond To Requests For Information And Input As Necessary.

Dates: 
1.	The Introductory Meeting Will Be Held On August 6, 2010 @1:00 P.M.
2.	Board Meetings At Which The Contractor Will Be Present Will Occur On August 6th - 8th, At The Department Of The Interior, 1849 C Street, N.W., Room 6616, Washington, D.C. 20240, And From August 9th -  August 13th, U.S. Department Of The Interior, 381 Elden Street, 2nd Floor Conference Room, Herndon, Virginia 20170.  Telephonic Availability Of The Contractor Is Requested On August 14th 驴 15th. 
2. Travel: Is Required For August 6th 驴 13th.
3. The Government Will Provide The Draft Safety Report Material To The Reviewer As Soon As It Is Available.

Contracting Agency: Office Of Policy, Budget And Administration
Requirement Description:
Task 1:  The Reviewer Shall Review And Provide An Independent Peer Review Of The Draft Safety Report Currently Being Prepared By The Outer Continental Shelf (ocs) Safety Board. The Summary Peer Review Will Include The Reviewer Reading The Report And Providing Comments, Findings And Recommendations For Achieving The Objectives Of The 30 Day Report.  An Introduction Meeting To Discuss Logistics Will Be Held Prior To The Government Distributing The Materials.

驴	Include Comments, Findings And Recommendations For Achieving The Objectives Of The 30 Day Report.

Task 2:  In Addition To The Peer Review Report, The Reviewer Shall Provide Advice, Review Recommendations, Provide And/or Shape Potential Recommendations, Conduct Expert Interviews And Help With Implementation Of The Proposed Rules.
